            +b targeted at security."
        requirement_id "SVV-1-c"
        title "Boundary/Edge Condition, Stress and Malformed or Unexpected Input Tests"
        description "This requirement under IEC 62443-4-1 focuses on testing security requirements
            +b by evaluating boundary/edge conditions, stress, and handling of malformed or
            +b unexpected inputs. Although these tests are not specifically targeted at
            +b security, they are crucial for ensuring the robustness of a system and its
            +b resilience against potential security threats that exploit these conditions."
        [ key_aspects
            "Boundary/Edge Condition Testing: Verifying system behavior at the limits of input ranges to ensure it handles extreme cases gracefully."
            "Stress Testing: Evaluating system performance and stability under peak load conditions to identify potential weaknesses that could be exploited in security scenarios."
            "Malformed or Unexpected Input Testing: Assessing the system's ability to handle unexpected or incorrect inputs without crashing or exposing vulnerabilities."
        [ related_standards
            {
                standard "ISO/IEC 27034-1"
                reference "This standard provides guidelines for application security, including ensuring
                    +b that applications can withstand unexpected input and stress conditions."
            {
                standard "NIST SP 800-53"
                reference "Control SI-10 (Information Input Validation) emphasizes the importance of
                    +b validating input data to prevent malicious data from exploiting system
                    +b vulnerabilities."
            {
                standard "OWASP Testing Guide"
                reference "The OWASP Testing Guide includes specific sections on input validation and
                    +b boundary testing, highlighting the importance of these tests in identifying
                    +b security vulnerabilities."
            {
                standard "ISO/IEC 25010"
                reference "This standard on system and software quality models includes aspects of
                    +b reliability and robustness, which are relevant to stress and boundary testing."
    {
        practice "5"
        code "SVV-2"
        name "Threat mitigation testing"
        sub "a) creating and executing plans to ensure that each mitigation implemented to
